Compute the determinant of the following two matrices and determine if they are invertible based on your result:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
A=\begin{bmatrix}1 & 2\\
3 & 6
\end{bmatrix},\text{ and }B=\begin{bmatrix}2 & 3\\
4 & 5
\end{bmatrix}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Solution
The determinant of 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $1\times6-2\times3=0$
\end_inset

.
 Thus,
 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is not invertible.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Solution
The determinant of 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $2\times5-3\times4=-2$
\end_inset

.
 Thus,
 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 is invertible.
\end_layout

